  "prompt": "What's the best way to calculate percentage off of something?",
  "response": "To calculate the percentage off of something, you'll want to determine the discount amount and then find out what that amount is as a percentage of the original price. Here are the steps to do so:\n\n1. **Determine the Discount Amount:** Subtract the discounted price from the original price.\n   \\[\n   \\text{Discount Amount} = \\text{Original Price} - \\text{Discounted Price}\n   \\]\n\n2. **Calculate the Percentage Off:**\n   - Divide the discount amount by the original price.\n   - Multiply the result by 100 to convert it to a percentage.\n   \\[\n   \\text{Percentage Off} = \\left( \\frac{\\text{Discount Amount}}{\\text{Original Price}} \\right) \\times 100\n   \\]\n\n**Example:**\nIf an item originally costs $80 and is now $60, calculate the percentage off:\n\n- Discount Amount = $80 - $60 = $20\n- Percentage Off = \\((\\frac{20}{80}) \\times 100 = 25\\%\\)\n\nThus, a $20 discount on an $80 item is a 25% discount.",
